@ifhtml
@heading Say for Speech Dispatcher
@end ifhtml

@code{spd-say} is a very simple client to Speech Dispatcher that takes some text from the
command line and even some simple parameters and passes these to Speech Dispatcher
for synthesis. The resulting syntesized speech is then played on your speakers.

Usage: @code{spd-say [options] "some text"}


@table @code
@item -r or --rate
Set the rate of the speech (between -100 and +100, 0 is default).
@item -p or --pitch
Set the pitch of the speech (between -100 and +100, 0 is default).
@item -i or --volume
Set the volume (intensity) of the speech (between -100 and +100, 0 is default).
@item -o or --output-module
Set the output module.
@item -l or --language
Set the language. The parameter is an iso language code, like @code{en} or @code{cs}.
@item -t or --voice-type
Set the prefered voice type (male1, male2, male3, female1, female2,
female3, child_male, child_female).
@item -m or --punctuation-mode
Set the punctuation mode (none, some, all).
@item -s or --spelling
Spell the message
@item -v or --version
Print version and copyright info.
@item -h or --help
Print a short help.
@end table

